    <fr-coverage>FR-15 (orchestrator now resolves node-output references — prerequisite for /narrate end-to-end)</fr-coverage>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    **REVISED 2026-06-29 — TWO-LAYER design (operator-approved after T110 deeper audit).**

    T110 audit found NodeOutputs infrastructure ALREADY exists in PlaybookRunContext, but the
    AI executors (AiCompletion + AiAnalysis) only read `templateParameters` from configJson —
    they ignore `inputBinding.X` which is the playbook author convention. Two distinct concerns
    need centralization:

    LAYER 1 (universal): extract `PlaybookTemplateContextBuilder.Build(runContext)` and wire
    orchestrator's `ApplyConfigJsonTemplates` to use `ITemplateEngine.Render` with it. Every
    executor's configJson gets `{{X}}` substitution at the string level (NodeOutputs +
    Parameters + run bag context). Existing `LoadKnowledgeNodeExecutor` + `ReturnResponseNodeExecutor`
    BuildTemplateContext methods refactored to call the shared helper (eliminates duplication).

    LAYER 2 (AI-shared): NEW `AiPromptInputBindingResolver` helper used by AiCompletion +
    AiAnalysis. Reads `configJson.inputBinding.<key>` (resolved values from Layer 1), looks up
    `action.input[<key>].placeholder` for the LLM-prompt placeholder name, populates
    `templateParameters` dict that PromptSchemaRenderer consumes. Centralizes AI-specific
    mapping so future AI executors get it free with one helper invocation — NOT per-executor
    template code.

    Rationale: addresses operator concern (2026-06-29) about needing to "code outputs for every
    executor". Future narrative-output executors throughout Workspace UX get template resolution
    for free via Layer 1, AI prompt-input mapping for free via Layer 2.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in C# generics, Handlebars.NET, and the BFF playbook
    orchestrator. Follow ADRs strictly. Match the existing TemplateEngine's "graceful on missing"
    contract — don't throw on unresolved bindings.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `PlaybookOrchestrationService` injects `ITemplateEngine`, calls `Render` (not literal Replace)
    against a merged Parameters + NodeOutputs context dict. `RunContext` carries `NodeOutputs`.
    Subsequent-node configJson resolution now sees prior nodes' OutputVariable values. xUnit
    tests prove behavior. Build passes; existing orchestrator tests pass (no regression).
  </goal>

