    <patterns>
      <pattern name="ITemplateEngine usage (existing call sites)" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Delivery/EmailTemplateService.cs">
        EmailTemplateService + WordTemplateService both inject ITemplateEngine and call Render(template, contextDict). Follow this exact pattern in the orchestrator.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="JsonElement → traversable conversion" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/TemplateEngine.cs">
        TemplateEngine.ConvertJsonElement(JsonElement) returns Dictionary/List/primitive — call this on NodeOutput.StructuredData before registering in NodeOutputs (so Handlebars can traverse `{{nodeName.field.subfield}}`).
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Today the orchestrator's `ApplyConfigJsonTemplates` only handles `{{paramName}}` literal substitution from the BFF's parameter dictionary. The deployed `DAILY-BRIEFING-NARRATE` playbook uses `{{json start}}`, `{{tldrResult.summary}}`, `{{channelRegistry.channels}}` — all of which need the existing Handlebars-backed `ITemplateEngine`. Wave 11 task 110 designed the wiring; this task implements it.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="110" status="must-complete-first">Design doc with proposed signatures + lifecycle.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 112 (helpers) and 114 (fan-out) build on this task's NodeOutputs surface.</item>
      <item>Task 115 (restore ValidateEntityNames config) requires this task complete so source-correct templates can actually resolve.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL · 📋 REASON: bff-api code-impl, modifies multiple .cs, downstream deps · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context + design doc from 110">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + design doc from task 110 (especially REVISION 2026-06-29 — Two-Layer Architecture section) + bff-extensions.md + ADR-010 + ADR-013.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Layer 1: Create PlaybookTemplateContextBuilder helper">
      NEW file `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookTemplateContextBuilder.cs` with static `Build(runContext)` returning `Dictionary&lt;string, object?&gt;`. Mirrors the pattern from `ReturnResponseNodeExecutor.BuildTemplateContext` lines 312-339: walks `runContext.NodeOutputs` calling `TemplateEngine.ConvertJsonElement` on StructuredData (or TextContent fallback), adds `runContext.Parameters` (Parameters win on collision), adds `run` metadata bag {id, playbookId, tenantId, completedAtUtc, startedAt}.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Layer 1: Inject ITemplateEngine + rewrite ApplyConfigJsonTemplates">
      Inject `ITemplateEngine` into `PlaybookOrchestrationService` constructor (already DI-registered at AnalysisServicesModule.cs:860). Rewrite `ApplyConfigJsonTemplates` (line ~1921) to (a) take `runContext` instead of just `parameters`, (b) build merged context via `PlaybookTemplateContextBuilder.Build(runContext)`, (c) call `_templateEngine.Render(node.ConfigJson, context)`. Preserve early-exit for `!ConfigJson.Contains("{{")`. Update call site at line 1198 to pass runContext.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Layer 1: Refactor duplicate BuildTemplateContext methods">
      `LoadKnowledgeNodeExecutor.BuildTemplateContext` (line ~277) and `ReturnResponseNodeExecutor.BuildTemplateContext` (lines 312-339) are byte-for-byte duplicates. Replace BOTH with calls to `PlaybookTemplateContextBuilder.Build(...)`. NOTE: existing per-executor `_templateEngine.Render` calls become NO-OPs for templates already resolved by the orchestrator at Step 3 — but the executors keep their own logic for "build output FROM resolved values" (passthrough output, terminal response). This eliminates duplication without breaking existing tests.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Layer 2: Create AiPromptInputBindingResolver helper">
      NEW file `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/AiPromptInputBindingResolver.cs` (static class or free helper). Method `PopulateTemplateParameters(configJsonInputBinding, actionInputs, templateParameters)` reads `configJson.inputBinding.&lt;key&gt;` (already resolved values from Layer 1), looks up `action.input[&lt;key&gt;].placeholder` for the LLM-prompt placeholder name, populates the `templateParameters` dict. Defensive: missing inputBinding → no-op; missing action.input mapping → log warning, skip.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Layer 2: Wire AiCompletionNodeExecutor to invoke the AI helper">
      In `AiCompletionNodeExecutor.ExecuteAsync` (around line 302 where `ExtractTemplateParameters` is called): AFTER extracting templateParameters from configJson, BEFORE calling PromptSchemaRenderer, invoke `AiPromptInputBindingResolver.PopulateTemplateParameters(configJson.inputBinding, context.Action.Inputs, templateParameters)` to merge inputBinding-derived values into templateParameters. The PromptSchemaRenderer then sees BOTH templateParameters values + inputBinding-derived values keyed by action input placeholder names.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Layer 2: Wire AiAnalysisNodeExecutor to invoke the AI helper">
      Mirror Step 6 in `AiAnalysisNodeExecutor` — same insertion pattern (the executor mirrors AiCompletion per code-comments per task 001 audit). Confirm via grep that `ExtractTemplateParameters` pattern exists there too.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Write xUnit tests (Layer 1 + Layer 2)">
      NEW: `PlaybookTemplateContextBuilderTests.cs` (4-6 tests covering NodeOutputs traversal + Parameters merge + run-bag).
      NEW: `PlaybookOrchestrationService_TemplateResolutionTests.cs` (5 tests: (a) `{{paramName}}` regression, (b) `{{nodeA.field}}` resolves, (c) `{{nodeA.nested.deep}}` resolves, (d) `{{nonexistent}}` empty, (e) Parameters wins on collision).
      NEW: `AiPromptInputBindingResolverTests.cs` (5 tests: (a) happy path inputBinding→placeholder, (b) missing inputBinding → no-op, (c) missing action.input mapping → warn+skip, (d) multiple inputs each correctly mapped, (e) inputBinding value already-resolved string passes through).
      Refactor existing `ReturnResponseNodeExecutorTests` + `LoadKnowledgeNodeExecutorTests` if needed to confirm BuildTemplateContext extraction didn't regress behavior.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Run full BFF test suite + verify build">
      `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` + `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` — confirm new tests pass + zero regressions across orchestrator + LoadKnowledge + ReturnResponse + AiCompletion + AiAnalysis tests.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Step 9.5 — Quality gates">
      Invoke `/code-review` on changed/new files. Invoke `/adr-check`. Address any HIGH/CRITICAL before commit.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Update TASK-INDEX + current-task.md">
      Mark 111 ✅; advance current-task.md to next pending task (112).
    </step>
    <step order="12" name="Commit">
      Conventional commit. Body documents: two-layer architecture, files added (PlaybookTemplateContextBuilder + AiPromptInputBindingResolver), refactored duplicates (Load/Return), executor edits (AiCompletion + AiAnalysis), test coverage. State BFF placement decision per CLAUDE.md §10. Do NOT push — Wave 11 batch-pushes after T119.
    </step>
  </steps>

